# Documentation and Milestones

- Keep docs aligned with implementation details (routes, env vars, tools, and architecture).
- Prefer updating existing docs (`docs/prd.md`, `docs/tech-stack.md`, `docs/tdd.md`) over creating new files.
- When PRD and TDD conflict (e.g., project structure, endpoint paths, Docker vs pm2), TDD and CLAUDE.md are authoritative — they reflect the final design decisions.
- Use concise, actionable language and keep command examples runnable.
- When a major feature or milestone is completed, update `docs/architecture.md`.
- Do not add extra markdown docs unless explicitly requested.
